               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
              
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                    <title type="complete" cert="low" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1171Awdana">ʿAwda nagaśt</title> 
                    <textLang mainLang="gez" otherLangs="ar"/>
                    <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                      ምክንያተሰ፡ <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/> ውእቱ፡ እመ፡ <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>  ሎቱ፡ እንዝ፡ 
                      ይ <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/> ማተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወ <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/> ይፁር፡ ጠልሰማተ፡ አእሚሮ፡ 
                      <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/> 
                      ወከዋክብተ፡ ወበዊኦ፡ ቀኖና፡ ወእንዘ፡ ኢይ <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>  ወል፡ ልቡናሁ፡ ወእመ፡ ይገብሮ፡ ይሤንዮ፡ በዝ፡ ዓለም፡ ወበዘይመጽእ፡
                      ዓለም፡ ዘከመ፡ ፈቀደ፡ ልቡናሁ፡ ወለዝንቱ፡ ነገር፡ ተናገርዎ፡ ጠቢባን፡ ሰብእ፡ ኀቢሮሙ፡ በ፩፡ ቃል፡ ወረከቡ፡ በቍዔተ፡ ብዙኃን፡
                      ሰብእ፡ በዝንቱ፡ ነገር፡ እመ፡ ይገብርዎ፡ በከመ፡ ይቤ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ። <hi rend="rubric">ምዕራፍ፡</hi> እትናገር፡ መቅድመ፡ ነገራተ፡ ፊደል፡ እለ፡
                      ቦሙ፡ ነጥብ፡ እስመ፡ እሙንቱ፡ መሠረቱ፡ ወጕንዱ፡ ለኵሉ፡ ነገር፡
                    </incipit>
                    <note>The work deals with the virtues of characters and numbers, according to their
                      combinations and their relations to the planets. Many tables, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰንጠረጀ፡</foreign>,
                      representing these combinations are included throughout the text.
                      It was translated from Arabic. Many technical terms and entire passages,
                    especially magic invocations, are in Arabic written in Ethiopic script.
                    As the work is of Muslim origin, these invocations contain formulas referring to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7216Muhammad">Muḥammad</persName>.</note>
                  </msItem>
              
